-- China c.bank reaffirms stable policy, appropriate credit growth in 2014
-- 
-- Fri Jan 10, 2014 05:17AM EST
-- None



BEIJING, Jan 10 (Reuters) - China central bank reaffirmed on Friday that it will keep a prudent monetary in 2014 and maintain appropriate growth in credit and social financing.

The People's Bank of China also reiterated in a statement on its website that it will expand cross-border usage of China's yuan currency, while preventing risks from capital flows and deepening financial reforms.